{
  "text": "With the above caveats in mind, we focus our interpretations on the results observed in Scotland for rates of admissions and deaths overall. As we have demonstrated previously that the Alcohol Act was associated with a 2.6% decline in population consumption levels in Scotland [CITATION_1] , it was hypothesized that overall rates of alcoholrelated deaths and admissions in Scotland would also decline. Our results do not support this hypothesis, which might be explained in several ways.",
